==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Copula
<hw>Cop"u*la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., bond, band. See
<er>Couple</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Logic & Gram.)</fld> <def>The
word which unites the subject and predicate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>The stop which connects the
manuals, or the manuals with the pedals; -- called also
<altname>coupler</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Copulate</ent>⟦br⟧
